## ✅ DOM Best Practices

### 1. Cache DOM Queries
```js
// ❌ Bad — queries DOM on every call
function update() {
  document.querySelector("#count").textContent = count;
}

// ✅ Good — query once, reuse
const countEl = document.querySelector("#count");
function update() {
  countEl.textContent = count;
}
```

### 2. Batch DOM Updates (avoid layout thrashing)
```js
// ❌ Bad — read then write in a loop (forces reflow)
items.forEach(item => {
  const height = item.offsetHeight;  // read (forces reflow)
  item.style.height = height + "px"; // write
});

// ✅ Good — read all, then write all
const heights = items.map(item => item.offsetHeight);  // all reads
items.forEach((item, i) => item.style.height = heights[i] + "px"); // all writes
```

### 3. Use DocumentFragment for Bulk Inserts
```js
// ❌ Causes N reflows
items.forEach(item => ul.appendChild(createLi(item)));

// ✅ One reflow
const fragment = document.createDocumentFragment();
items.forEach(item => fragment.appendChild(createLi(item)));
ul.appendChild(fragment);  // single DOM update
```

### 4. Avoid `innerHTML +=`
```js
// ❌ Re-parses and rebuilds entire DOM
container.innerHTML += "<div>New Item</div>";

// ✅ Use insertAdjacentHTML
container.insertAdjacentHTML("beforeend", "<div>New Item</div>");
```

### 5. Clean Up Event Listeners
```js
// Always remove listeners when no longer needed
function handleClick(e) { ... }
btn.addEventListener("click", handleClick);

// On cleanup (e.g. component unmount)
btn.removeEventListener("click", handleClick);
```

